r1834 | francis.brosnan.bl.zquez | 2010-06-23 10:07:38 +0000 (Wed, 23 Jun 2010) | 17 lines

libaxl:
* [fix] Updated PyAxlNode internal references to hold a reference
  to the PyAxlDoc associated to fix the issue of accessing a axl.Node
  object returned by a python function that created the document
  but also finished that reference once the function finished. Added
  regression test (py_test_04) to reproduce bug and check fix introduced.

* [fix] Updated axl.Node.first_child, get_next, get_previous and
  get_parent to avoid using Py_BuildValue but to directly return reference
  created (fixes memory leak problem).

* [fix] Making axl.Node.set_child to flag to false "finish on
  gc state" based on parent node instead of child node.

* [fix] Making axl.Doc.root to flag the axl.Node reference configured to
  be not deallocated on finish gc.

