r1092 | francis.brosnan.bl.zquez | 2008-12-10 15:53:46 +0000 (Wed, 10 Dec 2008) | 11 lines

libvortex-1.1:
* [fix] Finished regression test to check VORTEX_EVENT_CHANNEL_START.
  (test 14-d). With this, it is finished the initial pull API 
  for vortex. GREAT!

* [fix] Making close notify to unlock before calling user space allowing
  to call to vortex_channel_notify_close on that function.

* [fix] Making VORTEX_EVENT_CHANNEL_CLOSE to accept the close request
  if the event is found to be masked.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1091 | francis.brosnan.bl.zquez | 2008-12-10 09:51:30 +0000 (Wed, 10 Dec 2008) | 5 lines

libvortex-1.1:
* [fix] Fixing VORTEX_EVENT_CHANNEL_START event when it is masked.
* [new] Added initial regression test to check channel start event.
  Still not complete.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1090 | francis.brosnan.bl.zquez | 2008-12-09 18:57:32 +0000 (Tue, 09 Dec 2008) | 16 lines

libvortex-1.1:
* [new] Added support for a global start channel handler. API added:

    - vortex_ctx_set_channel_start_handler

* [new] Updated pull API to emit a new event: VORTEX_EVENT_CHANNEL_START
  which allows to receive and handle notifications about incoming channel
  start requests. Updated pull API to include new functions that provided
  access to especific event data:
 
    - vortex_event_get_server_name
    - vortex_event_get_profile_content
    - vortex_event_get_encoding

  Still required to check this new support.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1089 | francis.brosnan.bl.zquez | 2008-12-09 18:09:51 +0000 (Tue, 09 Dec 2008) | 7 lines

libvortex-1.1:
* [new] Added regression test to check VORTEX_EVENT_CONNECTION_CLOSED and
  VORTEX_EVENT_CONNECTION_ACCEPTED events. Added new function to perform a
  connection reference count update without checking its status:

    - vortex_connection_uncheck_ref

