  if limit is reached. (1.0/1.1).

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1079 | francis.brosnan.bl.zquez | 2008-11-29 10:09:18 +0000 (Sat, 29 Nov 2008) | 4 lines

libvortex:
* [fix] Added more msg no sequences to check on test_02n. Applied to
  1.0/1.1

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1078 | francis.brosnan.bl.zquez | 2008-11-28 17:32:31 +0000 (Fri, 28 Nov 2008) | 11 lines

libvortex:
* [fix] General engine update to allow remote BEEP peers to reuse 
  MSG no in the range of 0..2147483647 while connecting to Vortex, 
  allowing to reuse those MSG numbers as long as they are replied.
  Thanks to Sam Roberts who reported and provided useful comments
  to fix this issue. Created a regression test to check new support
  introduced. Even having updated MSG number checking support 
  vortex will still use its current MSG number generation pattern
  (starting from 0 and going to 2147483647 by updating 1 unit).
  Applied updated to 1.0/1.1.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1077 | francis.brosnan.bl.zquez | 2008-11-27 14:33:15 +0000 (Thu, 27 Nov 2008) | 3 lines

